# clangd configuration (editor-agnostic; committed).
#
# Points clangd at the compile database produced by the Ninja "windows-tooling"
# preset (regenerate with scripts/gen_compile_commands.ps1). That database
# carries the USD / godot-cpp include paths and defines (NOMINMAX, etc.) for
# every source file, which is how clangd resolves headers and completions.
#
# The database (build/tooling) uses MSVC (cl); clangd usually detects the MSVC /
# Windows-SDK system headers on its own. Only if standard-library headers show
# as "file not found" do you need the MSVC environment -- launch the editor from
# "Developer PowerShell for VS 2022". Full setup: docs/building.md, section
# "Editor / IntelliSense setup".
CompileFlags:
  CompilationDatabase: build/tooling
